cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the problem of quantifying redundant information between random variables, which is a topic that falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the desired properties of the measure and proposes new measures, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of quantifying redundant information is also relevant in data science (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI).
